2015-04-03 22:48:41:fail to execute sql
2015-04-03 22:48:41:INSERT INTO Feedback (id, username, sentence_id, text, time, type) VALUES (NULL, "chengkaili", NULL, "(1) I asked students to participate. If they use Gmail to register, the verification email is sent to their spam folder in Gmail. Should fix this. other users may not be able to find the verification email.

(2) Username doesn't allow space or underline; and a response to "how you heard about this" is mandatory. These are too strict. ", "2015-04-03 22:48:41", "Reporting problem")
2015-04-03 22:51:36:fail to execute sql
2015-04-03 22:51:36:INSERT INTO Feedback (id, username, sentence_id, text, time, type) VALUES (NULL, "chengkaili", NULL, "(1) I asked students to participate. If they use Gmail to register, the verification email is sent to their spam folder in Gmail. Should fix this. other users may not be able to find the verification email.

(2) Username doesn't allow space or underline; and a response to "how you heard about this" is mandatory. These are too strict. 

(3) The instruction says "You have to select one of them. " but actually you can skip. ", "2015-04-03 22:51:36", "Reporting problem")
2015-04-03 22:52:55:fail to execute sql
2015-04-03 22:52:55:INSERT INTO Feedback (id, username, sentence_id, text, time, type) VALUES (NULL, "chengkaili", NULL, "(1) I asked students to participate. If they use Gmail to register, the verification email is sent to their spam folder in Gmail. Should fix this. other users may not be able to find the verification email.

(2) Username doesn't allow space or underline; and a response to "how you heard about this" is mandatory. These are too strict. 

(3) The instruction says "You have to select one of them. " but actually you can skip.

(4) This should go the end of the 1st para of instructions:  You can skip labeling a sentence by clicking the "Skip this sentence" button. ", "2015-04-03 22:52:55", "Reporting problem")
